@Weak
The "forEGone" that is attached to "conclusion" is a different word than FORGONE in the revealer. To forego is to lead or precede; hence, a foregone conclusion is one that has been reached even before evidence or argument occurs.
To forgo is to give up or relinquish, a different thing altogether.

